{
  "stem": "21786.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And my friend George Wassermann, W-A-S-S-E-R-M-A-N-N, hanged himself in Australia in 1960.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I'm a real survivor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I wrote a paper on it as an explanation, what probably happened-- happened to them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that's a sad memory.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyhow, there we lived quite nicely.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We have organized all the furnishing and everything what we had in it, from the trains which are standing in front of us, which were taking the Jewish furniture and furnishings into Germany, which we simply opened during the night.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we somehow accomplished something very unusual for Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I used--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Being hanged.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I used the words, for the first time, the words organized.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the camp survivor's slang, or in the camp slang, organization means stealing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It means you couldn't steal only so easily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You could, but you usually had to do it in presence of somebody else, or being in a group which would help you to achieve your goal, whatever it was, whether it was to bring some of the vegetable into the ghetto, or whether it was having to do this.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There I stayed literally up to the year 1943, where-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and I found a space in one of these relatively tall buildings for Theresien, which was next to the building which was already forbidden for us.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was a barrier, and that was where the-- the gendarmes had their headquarters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We called it the casino.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in the loft of that building, there was space, and I built there something which was called in French a [SPEAKING FRENCH].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You had to go through the roof, build a window and a room behind that, and I had to bring in some heat, which was kind of a small iron stove.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
